00:43:17,309 --> 00:43:21,229
Usually a 9:00 to 5:00 day is the
best time for policy and bookmaking.

492
00:43:22,147 --> 00:43:25,692
If you have to work nights, like
a liquor violation, just call in.

493
00:43:25,734 --> 00:43:28,111
Don't worry about
quotas right now.

494
00:43:28,195 --> 00:43:31,323
Couple of hooker collars
will keep it cool.

495
00:43:42,459 --> 00:43:44,544
Been holding this for you.

496
00:43:44,586 --> 00:43:47,089
It's from Jewish Max.

497
00:44:43,019 --> 00:44:45,522
First day on the precinct,
I get that.

498
00:44:48,275 --> 00:44:50,235
This is great, Frank.

499
00:44:53,030 --> 00:44:55,115
I can open up a whole can
of peas with this.

500
00:44:55,198 --> 00:44:56,783
It's scary.

501
00:44:57,993 --> 00:45:00,704
I wanna protect myself.

502
00:45:00,787 --> 00:45:02,956
- You know what we do with this?
- What?

503
00:45:03,040 --> 00:45:05,625
We take it to
Inspector Kellogg.

504
00:45:10,964 --> 00:45:14,342
Kellogg- Didn't he used
to be in plainclothes?

505
00:45:14,426 --> 00:45:17,971
He's the second-highest ranking cop
in the department of investigations.

506
00:45:18,055 --> 00:45:20,348
- So what?
- What do you mean, "so what?"

507
00:45:20,432 --> 00:45:22,684
I happened to be instrumental
in getting the man his job.

508
00:45:22,768 --> 00:45:24,853
He owes me.
You understand?

509
00:45:26,104 --> 00:45:28,356
He's the most honest cop
I know, Frank.

510
00:45:29,733 --> 00:45:32,986
Frank, trust me.

511
00:45:44,790 --> 00:45:49,503
Things like this were common
practice in the bad old days.

512
00:45:49,586 --> 00:45:51,838
Hard to believe
it's still going on.

513
00:45:55,550 --> 00:45:58,220
Serpico, don't you think
it's kind of stupid...

514
00:45:58,303 --> 00:46:01,139
taking an envelope from somebody
you didn't know?

515
00:46:06,228 --> 00:46:09,398
What was I supposed to do?
I mean, give me...

516
00:46:09,439 --> 00:46:12,609
How would I know what was in it
unless I took it?

517
00:46:12,692 --> 00:46:15,237
You have two alternatives.

518
00:46:15,278 --> 00:46:18,657
You can force me to take you to
the commissioner of investigations.

519
00:46:18,740 --> 00:46:20,992
He'll drag you in front
of a grand jury.

520
00:46:21,076 --> 00:46:24,538
- I don't want that.
- I can understand that.

521
00:46:24,621 --> 00:46:26,540
Word will get out.

522
00:46:26,623 --> 00:46:30,544
Before it's all over, they'll find
you face-down in the East River.

523
00:46:36,174 --> 00:46:39,594
- What's the other alternative?
- Forget it.

524
00:46:41,680 --> 00:46:43,932
Well, what do I do with this?

525
00:47:06,163 --> 00:47:08,290
Hey, Sarge?
You got a minute?

526
00:47:11,835 --> 00:47:14,796
Colored cop gave me this.
I didn't know what to do with it.

527
00:47:21,094 --> 00:47:23,930
Well, I'll send it on
to the Benevolent Association.

528
00:47:35,692 --> 00:47:37,652
Alfie, come on.

529
00:47:59,341 --> 00:48:01,301
Is that Bjoerling?

530
00:48:07,724 --> 00:48:09,684
No. It's DiStefano.

531
00:48:11,853 --> 00:48:14,439
I was sure it was Bjoerling.

532
00:48:21,571 --> 00:48:24,241
You could hear it
better over here.

533
00:48:25,158 --> 00:48:27,327
- That's an invitation, right?
- Right.

534
00:48:28,453 --> 00:48:29,913
For coffee.

535
00:48:30,997 --> 00:48:34,668
I'll have to take a rain check.
I'm due at the hospital.

536
00:48:34,751 --> 00:48:37,879
Why don't you call in sick?
Perfect place.

537
00:48:39,673 --> 00:48:40,882
Not me.

538
00:48:40,966 --> 00:48:43,218
What are you,
dedicated or somethin'?

539
00:48:43,301 --> 00:48:48,014
That's right, I'm dedicated.
Most men can't stand it.

540
00:48:48,056 --> 00:48:51,351
- Well, what do they know?
- I like your garden.

541
00:48:57,482 --> 00:48:58,900
Love my garden.

542
00:49:00,235 --> 00:49:02,946
Okay. I love your garden.

543
00:49:04,406 --> 00:49:06,366
You know what they say,
don't you?

544
00:49:07,659 --> 00:49:09,244
No. What do they say?

545
00:49:09,870 --> 00:49:13,415
If you love a man's garden,
you gotta love the man.

546
00:49:19,921 --> 00:49:21,840
You like her, Alfie?

547
00:49:23,383 --> 00:49:26,053
All I can tell you, sir,
is I gave it back.

548
00:49:26,136 --> 00:49:28,555
I gotta get out of the 93.

549
00:49:28,597 --> 00:49:31,933
Well, what happened on
your narcotics application?

550
00:49:32,017 --> 00:49:35,979
Looked like it was set, until
I told 'em I was in plainclothes.

551
00:49:36,063 --> 00:49:37,856
It was like
the kiss of death.

552
00:49:37,898 --> 00:49:41,193
They think everybody in clothes
is on the take.

553
00:49:41,234 --> 00:49:43,904
Sir, do you know anything about
the Bronx 7th Division?

554
00:49:43,987 --> 00:49:47,949
I can go there if I want,
but if it's the same shit, screw it.

555
00:49:48,033 --> 00:49:51,495
I'd rather answer phones for Spanish
communications unit and go nuts.

556
00:49:51,578 --> 00:49:53,163
Come on, Alfie.

557
00:49:54,915 --> 00:49:57,876
Frank, did anyone
ever tell you...

558
00:49:57,959 --> 00:50:00,545
that you have a tendency
toward self-pity?

559
00:50:02,839 --> 00:50:04,674
No, you're the first.

560
00:50:04,758 --> 00:50:08,261
All right. Frank, I have
a friend up there, Roy Palmer.

561
00:50:08,345 --> 00:50:12,474
He's an administrative officer.
I'll speak with him.

562
00:50:12,557 --> 00:50:14,851
- Good. Thank you, sir.
- Good-bye, Frank.

563
00:50:14,893 --> 00:50:17,062
- God bless you.
- Right.

564
00:50:26,071 --> 00:50:28,699
Frank, Captain McCIain here.

565
00:50:28,782 --> 00:50:30,867
Captain McCIain. Could you
hold on a minute please, sir?

566
00:50:30,951 --> 00:50:32,369
Sure.

567
00:50:38,917 --> 00:50:41,378
Yeah. Sorry.

568
00:50:41,420 --> 00:50:43,380
I saw Inspector Palmer tonight...

569
00:50:43,422 --> 00:50:46,967
and he assures me the 7th Division
is as clean as a hound's tooth.

570
00:50:47,050 --> 00:50:49,428
His words, Frank.
"Clean as a hound's tooth."

571
00:50:50,262 --> 00:50:53,223
I told him he was getting
a hardworking officer...

572
00:50:53,306 --> 00:50:57,269
wears a beard, speaks Spanish and
would make a superb undercover man.

573
00:50:57,310 --> 00:50:58,562
He was delighted.

574
00:50:58,645 --> 00:51:02,649
That's good news, sir.
Thank you. Thank you very much.

575
00:51:02,733 --> 00:51:04,735
Good-bye, Frank.
God bless.

576
00:51:07,362 --> 00:51:09,948
When did you start doing that?

577
00:51:11,742 --> 00:51:14,077
McCIain says that Palmer says...

578
00:51:14,119 --> 00:51:16,538
that the 7th is as clean
as a hound's tooth.

579
00:51:17,789 --> 00:51:20,751
Well, if that's true,
your problems are over.

580
00:51:25,964 --> 00:51:27,924
Plainclothes division.

581
00:51:29,760 --> 00:51:31,178
Upstairs.

582
00:51:42,147 --> 00:51:44,775
- How are you? Good to see you!
- All right.

583
00:51:44,858 --> 00:51:46,902
We heard you were
coming up here. Listen.

584
00:51:46,985 --> 00:51:50,113
Say hello to Nate Smith.
Frank Serpico.

585
00:51:50,197 --> 00:51:53,033
- Jamie Morales, Frank Serpico.
- Serpico?

586
00:51:54,117 --> 00:51:56,453
Hey, babe, you're gonna
love it up here. It's beautiful.

587
00:51:56,536 --> 00:51:58,580
Listen, take-
I'll see youse later, all right?

588
00:51:58,663 --> 00:52:01,041
Take a little ride with me.
Get the feel of the division.

589
00:52:01,083 --> 00:52:03,126
- Maybe I should check in first.
- Fuck that. Come on.

590
00:52:04,628 --> 00:52:08,382
Deckk the halls
with boughs ofholly

591
00:52:12,969 --> 00:52:16,640
Ten grand, Dallas-
if Minnesota. Right.

592
00:52:16,723 --> 00:52:18,392
Green Bay, 12 and a half at...

593
00:52:19,101 --> 00:52:22,437
You dumb fuck.
We told you this location's hot.

594
00:52:22,479 --> 00:52:24,523
We told you to stay the fuck
out of here.

595
00:52:24,606 --> 00:52:27,359
Keough, nobody told me.
Honest.

596
00:52:27,442 --> 00:52:29,486
Bullshit.

597
00:52:29,569 --> 00:52:31,321
Come on.
Let's take a walk.

598
00:52:31,405 --> 00:52:33,657
Hi, kid.
All right, a C-note apiece.

599
00:52:33,740 --> 00:52:37,786
No way. We got a complaint.
Right, Frank? Come on.

600
00:52:37,869 --> 00:52:40,038
All right.
Make it 200, Keough.

601
00:52:40,122 --> 00:52:42,958
Hey, what, are you getting cheap
in your old age, bambino?

602
00:52:43,041 --> 00:52:45,669
- Three.
- Three?

603
00:52:45,752 --> 00:52:47,379
You heard me.

604
00:52:48,463 --> 00:52:51,675
- All right, three.
- I'll make it a light one.

605
00:52:54,970 --> 00:52:58,598
- You wanna write this up?
- No, I'm gonna check in.

606
00:52:58,682 --> 00:53:00,600
Take the collar, Frank.
Get on the sheet.

607
00:53:00,684 --> 00:53:02,102
I better check in.

608
00:53:04,104 --> 00:53:07,399
We're gonna have
a little talk later, right?

609
00:53:10,861 --> 00:53:13,947
That dumb schmuck only came up with
two bills because I booked him?

610
00:53:16,825 --> 00:53:18,326
Here you go, Frank.

611
00:53:18,410 --> 00:53:20,996
It was your collar.
Keep it.

612
00:53:22,456 --> 00:53:24,958
I had a hunch
you weren't gonna take it.

613
00:53:26,126 --> 00:53:29,504
You know, Frankie, we got a call
about you from downtown.

614
00:53:29,588 --> 00:53:31,214
Now, I ain't sayin' who.

615
00:53:31,298 --> 00:53:33,925
They just said you couldn't
be trusted, you know?

616
00:53:35,010 --> 00:53:37,804
- Because I don't take money, right?
- Come on, Frank.

617
00:53:37,888 --> 00:53:40,390
Let's face it. Who can trust
a cop who don't take money?

618
00:53:41,349 --> 00:53:43,935
I mean, you are pretty weird,
you know, kid?

619
00:53:44,019 --> 00:53:46,772
And with that call, the guys
were gettin' a little worried.

620
00:53:46,855 --> 00:53:49,649
I told them you were okay.
I knew you from the old 21.

621
00:53:49,733 --> 00:53:53,070
You'd never hurt
another cop, right?

622
00:53:54,029 --> 00:53:57,074
You'd never hurt another cop,
would you, Frank?

623
00:53:57,157 --> 00:53:59,951
- That'd depend on what he did.
- That's the wrong answer, Frankie.

624
00:54:05,791 --> 00:54:07,501
We're not doing
anything bad here.

625
00:54:07,584 --> 00:54:10,253
We're skimming
a little gambling money.

626
00:54:10,337 --> 00:54:13,340
It's clean. It's not dope.
It hurts nobody.

627
00:54:13,423 --> 00:54:15,342
Come on, Frank.

628
00:54:15,425 --> 00:54:18,720
Gamblers are gentlemen, and
they're gonna operate anyhow, right?

629
00:54:18,804 --> 00:54:21,306
Look, Keough, you don't have to
explain yourself to me.

630
00:54:21,390 --> 00:54:24,518
Do what you got to do.
Want some tea?

631
00:54:24,601 --> 00:54:27,562
No, I don't like that shit.
I'll have a coffee, huh?

632
00:54:27,646 --> 00:54:30,273
What's the matter, Frank?
What are you worried about?

633
00:54:30,315 --> 00:54:33,652
Listen.
We don't go overboard here.

634
00:54:33,735 --> 00:54:35,737
We're not sloppy.
We're careful.

635
00:54:35,779 --> 00:54:39,116
The spicks, niggers, we bust them.
They operate so dumb and sloppy...

636
00:54:39,157 --> 00:54:41,284
they get your ass
in hot water every time.

637
00:54:41,326 --> 00:54:43,870
But the Italians, now,
that's a different story.

638
00:54:43,954 --> 00:54:47,165
They're men of their word.
They're reliable, Frankie.

639
00:54:47,249 --> 00:54:50,544
- You really got it analyzed.
- Fuckin' right I got it analyzed.

640
00:54:50,627 --> 00:54:52,295
It's worth it.

641
00:54:53,380 --> 00:54:55,882
You know how much
the nut's running now, Frankie?

642
00:54:58,009 --> 00:55:02,013
- No, I wouldn't know that.
- $800 a month.

643
00:55:02,097 --> 00:55:06,518
That's 800 clams every time your
girlfriend gets the curse tax free.

644
00:55:07,352 --> 00:55:10,355
Here's the beauty. You don't
get it for the first eight weeks...

645
00:55:10,439 --> 00:55:13,150
till the guys get to
know you and you're okay.

646
00:55:13,233 --> 00:55:15,861
But you don't lose, either, 'cause
you get it on the other end...

647
00:55:15,944 --> 00:55:18,655
when you leave the division.

648
00:55:18,739 --> 00:55:21,783
Frankie, it's like-
it's like severance pay.

649
00:55:23,368 --> 00:55:26,496
Think it over, all right?
In or out.

650
00:55:29,332 --> 00:55:31,877
Look at me. I'm shaking.

651
00:55:35,964 --> 00:55:38,300
All my life I wanted
to be a cop, you know?

652
00:55:38,383 --> 00:55:40,761
It's like I can remember
nothing else.

653
00:55:44,389 --> 00:55:46,433
I remember this one time...

654
00:55:47,809 --> 00:55:49,770
there was...

655
00:55:49,853 --> 00:55:52,355
Somethin' happened.
A domestic argument or somethin'.

656
00:55:52,439 --> 00:55:54,358
Somebody stabbed somebody.

657
00:55:55,400 --> 00:55:57,819
And...

658
00:55:57,861 --> 00:56:00,447
there was this crowd
around this tenement.

659
00:56:01,490 --> 00:56:04,868
I must have been nine,
ten years old. I was this big.

660
00:56:04,951 --> 00:56:06,870
I went over to see
what was going on.

661
00:56:06,953 --> 00:56:10,165
I noticed the red light
goin' around and around...

662
00:56:10,207 --> 00:56:12,667
all these people,
and I couldn't see.

663
00:56:13,710 --> 00:56:17,214
I kept saying, "Do you know
what's goin' on? Do you know?"

664
00:56:17,297 --> 00:56:19,466
Nobody knew.

665
00:56:19,549 --> 00:56:22,719
It was like a big mystery
behind that...

666
00:56:22,803 --> 00:56:24,429
that crowd there.

667
00:56:25,514 --> 00:56:27,933
All of a sudden...

668
00:56:28,016 --> 00:56:30,060
the crowd just parted...

669
00:56:30,143 --> 00:56:32,479
Like the Red Sea, you see?

670
00:56:32,562 --> 00:56:36,149
And there were these guys
in blue, and I said...

671
00:56:36,191 --> 00:56:38,026
"They know."

672
00:56:39,111 --> 00:56:42,155
What do they know?
What do they know?

673
00:56:47,452 --> 00:56:49,621
It's amazing.

674
00:56:49,705 --> 00:56:51,665
It's incredible...

675
00:56:52,749 --> 00:56:55,711
but I feel like a criminal
'cause I don't take money.

676
00:56:59,798 --> 00:57:02,300
You get so tense
when you talk about it.

677
00:57:02,384 --> 00:57:03,802
I wonder why.

678
00:57:03,885 --> 00:57:05,470
Come here.

679
00:57:09,641 --> 00:57:11,518
- Right there.
- Here?

680
00:57:13,270 --> 00:57:16,606
I'm gonna ask you
a question, okay?

681
00:57:16,648 --> 00:57:18,942
Do you like cops?

682
00:57:19,026 --> 00:57:20,986
You're my first.

683
00:57:22,654 --> 00:57:26,033
No, I mean all this shit I've been
telling you. Do you believe it?

684
00:57:26,116 --> 00:57:27,701
Why not?

685
00:57:29,119 --> 00:57:31,663
- Does it shock you?
- Not much.

686
00:57:32,748 --> 00:57:35,375
What's the matter with me?

687
00:57:35,459 --> 00:57:37,544
Everybody knows about cops.

688
00:57:38,628 --> 00:57:41,256
Did you ever hear the story
of the wise king?

689
00:57:41,339 --> 00:57:44,468
Nope, but I got the feeling
I'm gonna hear it.

690
00:57:45,552 --> 00:57:49,973
Well, there was this king,
and he ruled over his kingdom.

691
00:57:50,057 --> 00:57:53,477
Right in the middle of the kingdom
there was a well.

692
00:57:53,518 --> 00:57:55,520
That's where everybody drank.

693
00:57:55,604 --> 00:57:59,232
One night,
this witch came along...

694
00:57:59,316 --> 00:58:01,234
and she poisoned the well.

695
00:58:02,319 --> 00:58:05,447
And the next day, everybody drank
from it except the king...

696
00:58:05,530 --> 00:58:07,616
and they all went crazy.

697
00:58:07,657 --> 00:58:09,951
They got together
in the street and they said...

698
00:58:10,035 --> 00:58:12,996
"We got to get rid of the king,
'cause the king is mad."

699
00:58:15,332 --> 00:58:18,585
And then that night, he went down
and he drank from the well.

700
00:58:18,668 --> 00:58:21,463
And the next day
all the people rejoiced...

701
00:58:21,505 --> 00:58:25,634
because their king
had regained his reason.

702
00:58:29,346 --> 00:58:31,306
I think you're trying
to tell me somethin'.

703
00:58:31,348 --> 00:58:33,183
- Me?
- Yeah.

704
00:58:35,227 --> 00:58:37,687
Hey, Frank, I want you
to say hello to somebody.

705
00:58:37,771 --> 00:58:41,692
- Drop your cocks and grab your socks!
- What the fuck is this?

706
00:58:43,402 --> 00:58:46,154
Frank Serpico,
say hello to Don Rubello.

707
00:58:46,238 --> 00:58:48,323
- He's gonna be your new partner.
- How you doin'?

708
00:58:49,908 --> 00:58:53,829
If you don't want to work with this
fucking nut for some reason, man...

709
00:58:53,870 --> 00:58:56,832
I'll buddy up with him,
all right?

710
00:58:56,915 --> 00:58:59,209
And go through all that crap
changing assignments?

711
00:58:59,292 --> 00:59:01,378
No. We'll be okay.

712
00:59:01,461 --> 00:59:03,296
We're paisans, huh?

713
00:59:06,216 --> 00:59:08,343
- What's with the fucking mouse?
- It's my partner.

714
00:59:08,427 --> 00:59:11,179
- Partner?
- He's specially trained, you know?

715
00:59:11,263 --> 00:59:14,391
He goes to track down heroin.

716
00:59:14,474 --> 00:59:17,144
Let him loose, goes into the hole,
picks it up, brings it back...

717
00:59:17,227 --> 00:59:19,688
sniffs it out,
brings it to you.

718
00:59:21,398 --> 00:59:24,151
- Yeah. I heard of that.
- You heard of that?

719
00:59:28,030 --> 00:59:31,158
This guy I'm looking for,
Vernon...

720
00:59:31,199 --> 00:59:34,286
He's a numbers collector who ain't
been meeting his obligations.

721
00:59:35,746 --> 00:59:39,291
He won't be hard to spot.
He's a mover. This is prime time.

722
00:59:42,836 --> 00:59:46,506
Since we're partners,
you gotta know the situation.

723
00:59:46,590 --> 00:59:50,635
Straight off.
I collect for the division...

724
00:59:50,719 --> 00:59:52,804
me and two other bagmen.

725
00:59:52,888 --> 00:59:55,348
That's what Keough
was sort of hinting at.

726
00:59:57,559 --> 01:00:00,312
Three of us pick up
the payoff twice a month.

727
