Ready on the right.
Ready on the left.

1192
01:37:39,279 --> 01:37:42,115
Ready on the firing line.

1193
01:38:31,289 --> 01:38:33,709
What are you gonna tell
the grand jury, Frankie?

1194
01:38:35,919 --> 01:38:38,046
Depends on
what they ask me.

1195
01:38:38,130 --> 01:38:40,590
Suppose they ask you
who's taking money?

1196
01:38:40,674 --> 01:38:42,926
What I don't know,
I don't know.

1197
01:38:43,010 --> 01:38:45,721
But you do know, Frank.

1198
01:38:45,804 --> 01:38:49,808
Look, Frankie, I like you. I don't
want to see anything happen to you.

1199
01:38:49,891 --> 01:38:54,229
But you gotta understand,
a lot of people could get hurt here.

1200
01:38:54,271 --> 01:38:57,858
I'm not saying anything's going to
happen. I'm saying it could happen.

1201
01:38:57,941 --> 01:39:00,736
I mean, there's lots ofways.
Nobody has to take a shot at you.

1202
01:39:00,777 --> 01:39:02,946
They can just not be there
when you need them.

1203
01:39:03,030 --> 01:39:06,241
Somebody come at you with a gun,
they look the other way.

1204
01:39:06,324 --> 01:39:08,410
Or they can send you
in first enough times...

1205
01:39:08,493 --> 01:39:10,704
until finally one day you're gonna
walk in the wrong door.

1206
01:39:14,833 --> 01:39:17,210
- Thanks for the information.
- Fuck you, Frank!

1207
01:39:20,505 --> 01:39:23,091
I have nothing more. Does anyone
have any further questions?

1208
01:39:24,176 --> 01:39:26,428
- Yes, Mrs. Crist?
- If I may, Mr. Knowles, thank you.

1209
01:39:26,511 --> 01:39:29,181
Officer Serpico came
to the 7th Division...

1210
01:39:29,264 --> 01:39:31,183
more than a year
and a half ago.

1211
01:39:31,266 --> 01:39:34,603
All during that time, the things
he's told us were taking place.

1212
01:39:34,686 --> 01:39:37,356
Now, why didn't
Officer Serpico...

1213
01:39:37,439 --> 01:39:41,485
report these criminal activities
when he first encountered them?

1214
01:39:41,568 --> 01:39:44,738
- I'd like to answer that.
- Mr. Chairman...

1215
01:39:44,780 --> 01:39:49,534
Mrs. Crist's question isn't material
or relevant to the present inquiry.

1216
01:39:49,618 --> 01:39:51,828
- Although I want to make it clear...
- I'd like to answer that.

1217
01:39:51,912 --> 01:39:55,499
Officer Serpico cannot be considered
derelict of his duty in any way...

1218
01:39:55,582 --> 01:39:57,876
or guilty of
any infraction of the law.

1219
01:39:57,959 --> 01:39:59,878
Quite the contrary.

1220
01:39:59,961 --> 01:40:03,465
The District Attorney is not prepared
to say any more at this time.

1221
01:40:03,548 --> 01:40:06,968
Very well. Officer Serpico,
thank you for your testimony.

1222
01:40:07,052 --> 01:40:10,055
This hearing is adjourned
until 10:00 tomorrow morning.

1223
01:40:11,640 --> 01:40:14,601
Why didn't you tell him
about Delaney and Kellogg?

1224
01:40:14,685 --> 01:40:17,479
Frank, this was a grand jury
about police officers...

1225
01:40:17,562 --> 01:40:20,232
actively engaged in corruption.

1226
01:40:20,315 --> 01:40:22,943
You don't implicate people
without sufficient evidence.

1227
01:40:23,026 --> 01:40:26,988
That's crap and you know it, because
even a dumb cop like me knows...

1228
01:40:27,030 --> 01:40:30,617
a prosecutor can take a grand jury
anywhere it wants to take it.

1229
01:40:30,701 --> 01:40:33,412
Now, you never led me anywhere
near the real problems...

1230
01:40:33,453 --> 01:40:36,748
Nothing about the bosses,
the brass...

1231
01:40:36,790 --> 01:40:39,668
how corruption like this could exist
without anybody knowing about it.

1232
01:40:39,751 --> 01:40:42,337
Now, a few flunky cops
in the Bronx. That's it.

1233
01:40:42,421 --> 01:40:45,090
None of the shit in Queens,
Brooklyn, Manhattan?

1234
01:40:45,173 --> 01:40:47,092
While you're at it,
why don't you mention Kansas City?

1235
01:40:47,134 --> 01:40:49,553
Well, "the biggest thing since
Harry Gross." That's what you said.

1236
01:40:49,636 --> 01:40:52,055
All right! Look, Frank.

1237
01:40:52,931 --> 01:40:55,892
You got guts, integrity.

1238
01:40:55,976 --> 01:40:58,937
There's going to be a detective's
gold shield in this for you.

1239
01:41:01,648 --> 01:41:05,110
Now, that's terrific.
That's good.

1240
01:41:05,193 --> 01:41:06,778
Maybe this is
what it's all about.

1241
01:41:06,862 --> 01:41:08,739
Maybe I should take my
gold shield and forget it.

1242
01:41:08,822 --> 01:41:11,116
I know you've been through
an ordeal, Frank.

1243
01:41:13,869 --> 01:41:17,372
I'm a marked man in this department.
For what?

1244
01:41:17,456 --> 01:41:20,792
- I've already arranged a transfer.
- To where? China?

1245
01:41:32,721 --> 01:41:35,474
That takes a 14-shot clip.

1246
01:41:35,557 --> 01:41:37,601
You expecting an army?

1247
01:41:37,642 --> 01:41:39,603
No, just a division.

1248
01:41:41,521 --> 01:41:46,068
Tauber, did you know I've had
reports about Serpico being a fag?

1249
01:41:46,151 --> 01:41:48,820
He used to hang out
in the BCI washroom.

1250
01:41:48,904 --> 01:41:52,115
That's stupid, Commissioner,
and you know it.

1251
01:41:52,199 --> 01:41:56,286
Mr. Commissioner, a gold shield
for Serpico at this time...

1252
01:41:56,370 --> 01:41:57,954
would convince
a lot of people...

1253
01:41:58,038 --> 01:41:59,581
Not while I'm commissioner.

1254
01:42:18,809 --> 01:42:20,227
Commander's office?

1255
01:42:22,688 --> 01:42:24,648
It's down that corridor.

1256
01:42:27,609 --> 01:42:30,362
Hey, Serpico. Do you know what
they're saying in the Bronx?

1257
01:42:30,445 --> 01:42:33,323
That you spilled your
guts to the grand jury.

1258
01:42:34,324 --> 01:42:36,284
Say it isn't so, Serpico.

1259
01:42:38,453 --> 01:42:40,122
It isn't so.

1260
01:42:41,206 --> 01:42:43,291
We know how to handle
guys like you.

1261
01:42:44,543 --> 01:42:46,503
I ought to cut
your tongue out.

1262
01:42:52,342 --> 01:42:54,052
Don't move.

1263
01:43:16,158 --> 01:43:18,410
Officer Serpico
reporting for duty, sir.

1264
01:43:26,668 --> 01:43:29,671
I'm Inspector Lombardo.
I want to shake your hand, Frank.

1265
01:43:31,465 --> 01:43:33,675
It's gonna be nice to have
a guy here I can trust.

1266
01:43:35,427 --> 01:43:36,887
Anybody in this command
you want to work with?

1267
01:43:40,474 --> 01:43:44,186
It's not who I want to work with.
It's who wants to work with me.

1268
01:43:47,022 --> 01:43:50,609
All right. You can't find anybody
you want to work with, Frank...

1269
01:43:50,692 --> 01:43:52,903
I'll work with you.

1270
01:43:52,986 --> 01:43:54,905
Is that all right?

1271
01:44:05,624 --> 01:44:07,626
How do we get past
the lookouts?

1272
01:44:07,709 --> 01:44:09,419
How many you got?
One.

1273
01:44:11,963 --> 01:44:14,591
There's two.

1274
01:44:14,675 --> 01:44:17,469
- Yeah, there's a guy.
- There's three of them.

1275
01:44:17,552 --> 01:44:19,721
It's four buildings away. We could
try to get down the fire escape.

1276
01:44:19,805 --> 01:44:21,890
Get in behind him.
What do you think?

1277
01:44:23,517 --> 01:44:25,852
- Look good to you?
- Yeah, let's go.

1278
01:45:08,895 --> 01:45:10,981
What do you think?
Want to try it?

1279
01:45:29,458 --> 01:45:31,710
- Oh, boy.
- You all right?

1280
01:45:31,752 --> 01:45:33,712
Yeah. I feel just
like a cop again.

1281
01:45:33,754 --> 01:45:36,048
- Let's go.
- Thank you.

1282
01:46:04,451 --> 01:46:06,036
Close up!

1283
01:46:08,872 --> 01:46:10,874
Wait, Frank!

1284
01:46:10,957 --> 01:46:12,417
Come on!

1285
01:46:21,843 --> 01:46:23,261
I ain't got nothing!

1286
01:46:25,472 --> 01:46:27,432
Beat it, fuck face!

1287
01:46:28,600 --> 01:46:32,062
Get the other one! Get out of here!
Get up against the wall.

1288
01:46:35,941 --> 01:46:38,235
What the hell's goin' on here?
Who the hell are you?

1289
01:46:38,276 --> 01:46:40,112
- Who are you?
- The police! Who the hell you think?

1290
01:46:40,195 --> 01:46:42,823
Get the fuck against the wall.
Up, up, up!

1291
01:46:42,906 --> 01:46:46,576
- Let me see your shield.
- All right. There's my shield.

1292
01:46:46,618 --> 01:46:49,287
- Where are you from?
- The borough. Manhattan 8th.

1293
01:46:49,371 --> 01:46:52,499
No, goddamn it! I just paid
the borough this morning!

1294
01:46:55,085 --> 01:46:56,753
What the hell kind of
shakedown is this?

1295
01:46:56,837 --> 01:46:58,922
Who'd you pay
in the borough?

1296
01:47:00,590 --> 01:47:03,093
Nobody.
I didn't pay no...

1297
01:47:03,135 --> 01:47:05,220
Who'd you pay
in the borough?

1298
01:47:05,303 --> 01:47:08,473
I didn't pay nobody.
Now let go of me.

1299
01:47:09,516 --> 01:47:14,104
We followed up,
and there's no doubt about it.

1300
01:47:14,187 --> 01:47:17,607
The pad here in Manhattan
is bigger...

1301
01:47:17,649 --> 01:47:22,404
and it's more sophisticated
than the one in the Bronx.

1302
01:47:22,487 --> 01:47:25,490
The pickups here are made-
You want to get this...

1303
01:47:25,574 --> 01:47:28,785
The pickups are made by...

1304
01:47:28,869 --> 01:47:31,747
retired policemen.

1305
01:47:31,788 --> 01:47:35,292
That way, no plainclothesmen
are directly involved.

1306
01:47:35,375 --> 01:47:39,629
Now, we need investigative help
on this one, Chief.

1307
01:47:41,465 --> 01:47:45,844
If you need investigative help
and you don't trust your own men...

1308
01:47:45,927 --> 01:47:48,930
why don't you requisition some
recruits from the police academy?

1309
01:47:57,230 --> 01:47:58,815
With all due respect,
sir...

1310
01:48:00,859 --> 01:48:03,779
backing us up is the only hope
the police department has got.

1311
01:48:03,820 --> 01:48:07,491
Good cops would come forward if they
thought there was encouragement...

1312
01:48:07,574 --> 01:48:09,910
in the department to do so, and if
they thought it would do any good.

1313
01:48:09,951 --> 01:48:11,912
If there's no encouragement,
they're not gonna do it.

1314
01:48:11,995 --> 01:48:15,540
I've done a lot more than most
people to defend and preserve...

1315
01:48:15,624 --> 01:48:19,044
the image of this department
and protect Commissioner Delaney...

1316
01:48:19,127 --> 01:48:23,006
against reckless and irresponsible
assaults from outside agencies.

1317
01:48:24,925 --> 01:48:26,843
That's it, huh?

1318
01:48:26,927 --> 01:48:30,597
I mean, that's what's
really important, isn't it?

1319
01:48:30,639 --> 01:48:32,766
That's what
you want to know...

1320
01:48:32,849 --> 01:48:36,103
what outside agencies
I've been to, right?

1321
01:48:37,646 --> 01:48:39,398
- Hello.
- Hello, prick.

1322
01:48:39,481 --> 01:48:41,608
- Who is this?
- Frank.

1323
01:48:42,484 --> 01:48:45,445
- How are you? Where are you?
- I'm ready to go to the Times.

1324
01:48:46,405 --> 01:48:50,492
It's a goddamn
serious step, Frank.

1325
01:48:50,575 --> 01:48:53,161
I don't know if
the timing is right.

1326
01:48:55,872 --> 01:48:58,667
Look, I want it to get on
the record, that's all...

1327
01:48:58,750 --> 01:49:01,169
in case something
should happen to me.

1328
01:49:04,715 --> 01:49:06,800
I want it on the record.

1329
01:49:09,845 --> 01:49:11,263
I don't know ifwe
carry enough weight.

1330
01:49:12,931 --> 01:49:15,017
I don't know if the New York Times
will go that far out on a limb...

1331
01:49:15,100 --> 01:49:17,352
on the say-so
of two flunky cops.

1332
01:49:21,648 --> 01:49:24,401
Suppose an inspector
were to come with us?

1333
01:49:26,028 --> 01:49:29,448
You know, I got 20 years
on the force.

1334
01:49:29,489 --> 01:49:33,827
Just bought this place.
I signed a 500-year mortgage on it.

1335
01:49:33,910 --> 01:49:37,122
- Turn that thing off out there!
- Come on. Everybody to bed.

1336
01:49:37,205 --> 01:49:39,249
- Aw, Mom!
- Turn that damn thing down!

1337
01:49:39,332 --> 01:49:41,251
Come on, now.
Go on upstairs.

1338
01:49:41,335 --> 01:49:43,378
You said we could go
to bed late!

1339
01:49:45,047 --> 01:49:47,966
This is against department
regulations, you both know that.

1340
01:49:48,050 --> 01:49:52,346
If they want to throw the book
at me, they can do it.

1341
01:49:52,387 --> 01:49:54,473
If I left the force...

1342
01:49:55,849 --> 01:49:57,976
I don't know
what I could do.

1343
01:50:03,774 --> 01:50:07,694
Okay, I made my little speech.
I'll back you up a hundred percent.

1344
01:50:11,698 --> 01:50:14,910
Times and the News.
I got the money, fellas.

1345
01:50:14,993 --> 01:50:16,912
Here you go, here you go,
here you go.

1346
01:50:16,995 --> 01:50:18,413
Newsweek, please.

1347
01:50:20,832 --> 01:50:22,751
Holy sh- Jeez!

1348
01:50:25,087 --> 01:50:26,713
Aw, Christ!

1349
01:50:26,797 --> 01:50:29,675
You could almost predict
the numbers they're gonna do.

1350
01:50:29,716 --> 01:50:31,968
Delaney's gonna issue
some phony denial.

1351
01:50:32,052 --> 01:50:35,013
Somebody from the mayor's office
will say something noble.

1352
01:50:35,097 --> 01:50:39,726
Delaney'll change his tune. Finally,
the mayor will appoint a commission.

1353
01:50:39,810 --> 01:50:42,979
"Mayor Lindsay announced the
formation of a five-man committee...

1354
01:50:43,063 --> 01:50:45,899
to review the city procedures for
investigating police corruption."

1355
01:50:45,982 --> 01:50:49,027
How come I'm not
in the first paragraph?

1356
01:50:49,111 --> 01:50:50,529
Unbelievable!

1357
01:50:54,825 --> 01:50:59,204
The Times' report smells
of the familiar smear tactics...

1358
01:50:59,287 --> 01:51:01,289
of McCarthyism.

1359
01:51:01,373 --> 01:51:05,836
- I have issued a statement-
- We here at city hall...

1360
01:51:05,919 --> 01:51:08,630
The mayor appointed a special
investigation commission...

1361
01:51:08,714 --> 01:51:10,632
to be headed
by Whitman Knapp.

1362
01:51:10,716 --> 01:51:12,134
Yeah, come.

1363
01:51:17,180 --> 01:51:22,644
It's your reward. It's a transfer
to narcotics, Brooklyn South.

1364
01:51:22,728 --> 01:51:25,856
You're still in clothes. You get
a tin shield, not a gold one.

1365
01:51:30,652 --> 01:51:32,571
I miss you already, Frank.

1366
01:51:37,617 --> 01:51:40,829
Look, Frank...

1367
01:51:43,540 --> 01:51:46,209
it's narcotics.

1368
01:51:46,293 --> 01:51:48,837
You be careful.

1369
01:51:48,879 --> 01:51:52,382
It's very easy to get hurt...

1370
01:51:53,925 --> 01:51:55,344
and to...

1371
01:51:56,928 --> 01:51:58,638
to be set up.

1372
01:52:40,681 --> 01:52:42,724
Get in.

1373
01:52:59,658 --> 01:53:01,743
You're not wired,
are you?

1374
01:53:02,869 --> 01:53:04,746
Okay, you cocksucker.

1375
01:53:06,248 --> 01:53:09,251
You might get by in the Bronx
with that kind of shit...

1376
01:53:09,334 --> 01:53:12,754
but down here,
800 a month is chicken feed.

1377
01:53:14,381 --> 01:53:17,134
Last week,
one dope dealer...

1378
01:53:17,217 --> 01:53:20,262
sent out these guys
making pickups.

1379
01:53:20,345 --> 01:53:22,848
40,000 each.

1380
01:53:22,931 --> 01:53:26,226
We let 'em collect it all,
and then hit 'em.

1381
01:53:26,309 --> 01:53:29,896
120,000 split four ways.

1382
01:53:30,939 --> 01:53:33,358
That's serious money.

1383
01:53:33,442 --> 01:53:36,987
And with that,
you don't fuck around.

1384
01:53:38,780 --> 01:53:41,158
- I got the message.
- Good.

1385
01:53:41,950 --> 01:53:43,410
Now get the fuck out.

1386
01:53:50,083 --> 01:53:51,501
The guy's name is Limbo.

1387
01:53:51,585 --> 01:53:53,920
He just uses this place,
his girlfriend's brother's place.

1388
01:53:53,962 --> 01:53:56,548
He's a pusher- heroin.

1389
01:53:56,631 --> 01:53:58,884
- We'll drive around to the corner.
- Right.

1390
01:53:58,967 --> 01:54:02,637
You keep in sight out front. When
you spot somebody who's dirty...

1391
01:54:02,679 --> 01:54:04,765
take off your glasses
and wipe 'em.

1392
01:54:04,848 --> 01:54:07,392
- Got it?
- Right. Okay.

1393
01:55:15,752 --> 01:55:18,213
We stay around here very long,
we're gonna get spotted.

1394
01:55:18,296 --> 01:55:21,883
Well, Frank, why don't you
go up there and check it out?

1395
01:55:21,967 --> 01:55:25,262
- Why don't you?
- I got the wrong clothes.

1396
01:55:25,345 --> 01:55:28,056
I'll take you shopping.

1397
01:57:12,703 --> 01:57:14,162
Limbo.

1398
01:57:47,571 --> 01:57:49,322
Police. Freeze!

1399
01:57:49,406 --> 01:57:51,408
Police officer.
All right, up against the wall.

1400
01:57:51,491 --> 01:57:55,704
Get your hands up against that wall.
Get up. All right.

1401
01:57:55,787 --> 01:57:58,707
- Palms on the wall and spread 'em.
- Get those hands up!

1402
01:57:58,749 --> 01:58:00,834
- Come on. Spread 'em!
- Get your feet apart.

1403
01:58:01,877 --> 01:58:03,879
- I saw the buy.
- Let's get Limbo.Julio!

1404
01:58:03,962 --> 01:58:06,214
- You all right, baby?
- Yeah, yeah. I got 'em.

1405
01:59:10,278 --> 01:59:12,155
Police officer!

1406
01:59:22,290 --> 01:59:24,251
What the fuck
are you waiting for?

1407
01:59:25,252 --> 01:59:27,379
Go down the fire escape!

1408
01:59:43,562 --> 01:59:47,232
Police! Throw out your guns
and come out with your hands up!

1409
02:00:21,475 --> 02:00:24,644
- Wait. What do you got here?
- It's Mr. and Mrs. Serpico, sir.

1410
02:00:24,728 --> 02:00:26,646
Okay. Go ahead.

1411
02:00:31,943 --> 02:00:34,905
- Where's our son?
- They're bringing him from X-ray.

1412
02:00:34,988 --> 02:00:37,449
- We want to see him.
- Just a few minutes.

1413
02:01:05,560 --> 02:01:07,479
Mr. and Mrs. Serpico...

1414
02:01:07,562 --> 02:01:11,650
the news is better
than we expected.

1415
02:01:11,733 --> 02:01:16,029
Thank God the bullet
was a small caliber.

1416
02:01:16,113 --> 02:01:17,698
It didn't enter the brain...

1417
02:01:19,366 --> 02:01:21,451
or strike the spinal cord.

1418
02:01:22,953 --> 02:01:25,497
He's on the critical list...

1419
02:01:25,539 --> 02:01:28,750
but his condition
seems to be stable.

1420
02:01:30,085 --> 02:01:31,920
Thank you, Doctor.
Thank you.

1421
02:02:05,871 --> 02:02:09,041
Stay out of there.
Didn't they tell you?

1422
02:02:09,124 --> 02:02:10,584
What?

1423
02:02:10,667 --> 02:02:14,046
The word is, don't talk to him.
He's no fuckin' good.

1424
02:02:23,889 --> 02:02:26,516
- How you doing, kid?
- Hello, Sid.

1425
02:02:33,231 --> 02:02:35,192
How are you?

1426
02:02:38,362 --> 02:02:40,781
You wanna read my fan mail?

1427
02:02:40,864 --> 02:02:42,783
Sure.

1428
02:02:42,866 --> 02:02:44,951
You're a big shot now, huh?

1429
02:03:13,188 --> 02:03:16,775
I want you to get those
fucking cops away from my door.

1430
02:03:27,577 --> 02:03:31,164
The Knapp Commission likes you.
They want you to appear.

1431
02:03:31,248 --> 02:03:32,749
Naturally.

1432
02:03:37,587 --> 02:03:39,047
Heinemann and Julio
are cleared.

1433
